John M. ALFORD, Appellant, v. ADDRESSOGRAPH-MULTIGRAPH CORPORATION, a Corporation, Appellee. No. 10698. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit June 2, 1944. Carlos G. Stratton, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Lyon & Lyon, Leonard S. Lyon, and Lewis E. Lyon, all of Los Angeles, Cal., and George H. Wallace and Charles B. Cannon, both of Chicago, 111., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeal in above cause be dismissed with prejudice, and without costs to either party, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly and that the mandate of this Court in this cause issue forthwith.
